    <section id="HowTo"><b>How I found this data</b>
    <br> I went to the Chicago Data Portal and compiled ten years of library visitor numbers into one google sheets. The google sheets and Chicago Data Portal are linked in the navigation bar.</section>
    <div class="mycontainer">
        
        <div><b><p>Line Graph</p></b><p>I calculated the sum of all the libraries total visitorship and inputted it into a Flourish line graph.</p></div>

    </div>
    <div class="mycontainer">
        
        <div><b><p>Map</p></b><p>I created a pivot table for the years 2013 and 2023 to find the number of visitors per zip code. I then searched for all the latitude and longitude coordinates for the library addresses and inputted them into the Flourish set.</p></div>

    </div>

    <div class="mycontainer">
        
        <div><b><p>Bar Chart and Bar Graph</p></b><p>I calculated the sum of each respective month and made a chart for the total visitors per month of the years 2013 and 2023. I then inputted the data into Flourish</p></div>

